== Boston Marathon Explosion ==
There was an explosion April 15th, 2013  <span style="font-size: smaller;" class="autosigned">— Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/140.107.157.245|140.107.157.245]] ([[User talk:140.107.157.245|talk]]) 20:21, 15 April 2013 (UTC)</span><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
: However, the edits were reverted for I guess being unreliably sourced, so I will provide a source here for someone to add later (I'd do it myself, but I can't make league edits on my iPad): [http://www.detroitnews.com/article/20130415/NATION/304150425/1020/rss09] '''<span style="text-shadow:#808080 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em">[[User:ZappaOMati|<font color="#0000FF">Zappa</font>]][[Special:Contributions/ZappaOMati|<font color="#00FF00">O</font>]][[User talk:ZappaOMati|<font color="#FF0000">Mati</font>]]</span>''' 22:16, 15 April 2013 (UTC)
There are two workers who said they heard an explosion. Rachel Flor (http://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2013/04/15/jfk-library-evacuated-after-explosion-fire-polie-probe-possible-link-marathon-blast/4gQintGxnUv8he2Ul8THLI/story.html) and Paul Yazbeck (http://www.bostonirish.com/news/2013/jfk-library-official-fire-was-not-caused-device). Yet everyone jumped into the "fire related" mantra. Are these workers lying? In my opinion, it's just incredible that even though no one knows who bombed the marathon and the investigation is far from closed, everyone is absolutely sure the library fire is unrelated. How can this possibly be assessed so quickly? No one knows what was damaged inside the library yet.  <span style="font-size: smaller;" class="autosigned">— Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/177.140.194.198|177.140.194.198]] ([[User talk:177.140.194.198|talk]]) 12:55, 16 April 2013 (UTC)</span><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
* Even if there was no explosion (though major media like the Daily Mail continue to report there was) the fact numerous media sources like CNN, based upon early statements by the police, reported an explosion should be included in the article.  In any event, are there any reports regarding damage? [[Special:Contributions/70.72.211.35|70.72.211.35]] ([[User talk:70.72.211.35|talk]]) 18:52, 16 April 2013 (UTC)

